  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Neha, I'm a tea person — nothing beats a quiet afternoon with a good cup. How's the design project coming along?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Slow. Too many meetings. chai than tea, but I get it."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Slow and too many meetings, that’s a rough combo. Chai’s the better choice, honestly. What part of the design feels stuck?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "User: The ideation phase. Everyone has opinions, no one agrees. It’s like herding cats."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Ideation with too many opinions is a minefield. Herding cats — I get it. What’s one idea everyone did like?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The color scheme. We all vibed on the palette — soft pastels with a pop of terracotta. But beyond that? Radio silence. *mumbles* Why is consensus so hard?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You nailed the color part — that’s a solid win. Consensus? It’s a tricky beast. What’s your go-to when ideas clash — compromise, or stick to your gut?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Compromise, most days. But it’s exhausting. Sometimes I think, why even have a gut if it’s just gonna get ignored? *sigh*"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Compromise daily is a lot — and that sigh hits hard. Gut vs group — what’s one small way you’ve kept your voice in the mix?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I take notes and revisit them later. Sometimes my ideas get lost in the noise, but at least they’re there if I need to pull them out. It’s not perfect, though — feels like a work in progress."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Notes as a silent advocate — smart move. Work in progress is still progress. What’s one idea you’d love to test but haven’t yet?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "A hidden micro-interaction — something subtle that guides the user without being obvious. Like a tiny animation that makes the app feel alive. But no one’s biting on it. *shrugs* Maybe I’m just a dreamer."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hidden micro-interactions are gold for user flow, they add soul. Shrugs don’t suit you, Neha. What’s stopping the team from trying it out?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Fear of failure, maybe? Or just not seeing the value in small wins. I get it. But sometimes the little things are the most memorable. *shrugs again* Maybe I’ll pitch it again when energy’s higher."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Fear of small wins is a silent drag, but you’re right, they matter. Pitch it when the energy’s high. What’s your sign that the mood’s right?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "When the room feels less like a meeting and more like a conversation. You know, when people start laughing at their own jokes and the coffee’s not even half gone. That’s my cue. *shrugs* Maybe I’ll bring cookies next time."
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Cookies? Now that’s a conversation starter. Laughter and half-coffee — perfect timing. What kind of cookies? Chocolate? Something else?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Butterscotch, with a hint of cardamom. Or maybe just a classic — chocolate chip. *shrugs* Maybe I’ll bring both. Who knows what’ll work."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Butterscotch, cardamom — now that's a bold move. Classic or bold, what's the plan if the pitch still falls flat?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I pivot to another project for now, or I keep pushing. It’s a tightrope walk. But sometimes, you just gotta walk the line. *shrugs* Maybe I’ll just keep baking until they listen."
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Pivot or push — both take courage. Baking your way to buy-in? Now that’s a plan with flavor. What’s next on your baking list?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm. Maybe something with rose and pistachio next? Or just stick with what works — cookies, chai, and hoping the room feels less like a meeting. *shrugs* Gotta go now. Talk later."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Rose and pistachio — sounds like a dream. Chai and good vibes first, meetings second. Talk soon, Neha!"
    }
  ],
